&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Consultant psychiatrist in General Adult Psychiatry, Eating Disorder&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;NELFT Community Eating Disorder Service&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;6 Programmed Activities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Service base: NELFT Community Eating Disorder Service, Orchards Health Centre, Gascoigne Road, Barking, IG11 7RS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an exciting consultant psychiatrist post in a multidisciplinary community eating disorder service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will assess and manage adult patients referred to the service. The service as a whole offers eating disorder assessment and treatment to both adults and children &amp; young people in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;the following four boroughs: Redbridge, Barking &amp; Dagenham, Havering and Waltham Forest. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be a member of the MDT and have the support of other team members in their clinical work. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;As the service is exclusively an outpatient service, the post holder will not hold an inpatient case load, but the post holder will work with specialist eating disorder inpatient units where patients are admitted to aid smooth transition to different levels of care. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
